[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 45/100 path 5/5 answer="Let's denote the amount Elvis saves each day in the first half of the month as \\(x\\). Therefore, he saves \\(2x\\) each day in the second half of the month to meet his goal. \n\nIn total, Elvis’s savings for the entire month consist of:\n\\[ (x + 2x) \\times 15 = 3x \\times 15 = 45x \\]\n\nWe know that the total amount saved should equal the required saving target of $1125, so we can set up the equation:\n\n\\[ 45x = 1125 \\]\n\nSolving for \\(x\\):\n\n\\[ x = \\frac{1125}{45} = 25 \\]\n\nTherefore, Elvis must save \\(2x\\) each day in the second half, which gives us:\n\n\\[ 2x = 2 \\times 25 = \\$50 \\]\n\nElvis has to save $\\boxed{50}$ dollars every day during the second half of the month."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 45/100 done id=gsm8k_test_541 prediction='750' gold='50' correct=False vote_counts={'750': 2, '18.75': 1, '16875': 1, "Let's denote the amount Elvis saves each day in the first half of the month as \\(x\\). Therefore, he saves \\(2x\\) each day in the second half of the month to meet his goal. \n\nIn total, Elvis’s savings for the entire month consist of:\n\\[ (x + 2x) \\times 15 = 3x \\times 15 = 45x \\]\n\nWe know that the total amount saved should equal the required saving target of $1125, so we can set up the equation:\n\n\\[ 45x = 1125 \\]\n\nSolving for \\(x\\):\n\n\\[ x = \\frac{1125}{45} = 25 \\]\n\nTherefore, Elvis must save \\(2x\\) each day in the second half, which gives us:\n\n\\[ 2x = 2 \\times 25 = \\$50 \\]\n\nElvis has to save $\\boxed{50}$ dollars every day during the second half of the month.": 1}
