[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 51/100 path 4/5 answer="Liam made $63 on his stand, so we divide this amount by the price per lemonade ($4) to find out how many lemonades he sold:\n$63 ÷ $4/lemonade = <<63/4=15.75>>15.75 lemonades\n\nMitchell sold 21 lemonades at $4 each, so we multiply this number by the price per lemonade:\n21 lemonades × $4/lemonade = $<<21*4=84>>84\n\nTo find out how many more dollars Mitchell made than Liam, we subtract Liam's earnings from Mitchell's earnings:\n$84 (Mitchell's earnings) - $63 (Liam's earnings) = $<<84-63=21>>21\n\nTherefore, Mitchell made $21 more than Liam that weekend."
