[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 66/100 path 1/5 answer='Mike originally has 600 movies. One third of them are in various series:\n\\[ \\frac{1}{3} \\times 600 = 200 \\text{ movies} \\]\n\nSo, the number of movies that are not part of these series is:\n\\[ 600 - 200 = 400 \\text{ movies} \\]\n\nOut of these, 40% are older movies priced at $5 each:\n\\[ 0.40 \\times 400 = 160 \\text{ older movies} \\]\n\nTherefore, the number of normal movies is:\n\\[ 400 - 160 = 240 \\text{ normal movies} \\]\n\nEach normal movie costs $10, so the total cost for the normal movies is:\n\\[ 240 \\times 10 = \\$\\boxed{2400} \\]'
