[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 78/100 path 5/5 answer="Let's denote the number of small stuffed animals sold as S and the number of large stuffed animals sold as L. We know that Teresa sells the small stuffed animals at $4 each, so:\n\nTotal earnings from small stuffed animals = 4S\n\nTeresa sells 2L small stuffed animals (twice as many) compared to the number of large stuffed animals she sells. Therefore:\n\nNumber of small stuffed animals = Number of large stuffed animals × 2\nS = 2L\n\nWe also know that Teresa makes $120 in total from selling both types of stuffed animals:\n\nTotal earnings = Earnings from large stuffed animals + Earnings from small stuffed animals\n\nEarnings from large stuffed animals = $120 - Earnings from small stuffed animals\n\nSubstituting the known values:\n\n$120 = ($12/L) × L + (4S)\n\nSince we have two expressions for S and one expression for L, let's solve these equations together:\n\nFirst, let's express everything in terms of S:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - ($12/L) × L\n\nNow, let's simplify and substitute S with 2L:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $24/L\n\nWe know L = S / 2, so substitute L back into the equation:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $24/(S/2)\n\nSimplify further:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $48/S\n\nMultiply through by S to clear the fraction:\n120S - 4S^2 = $120S - $48\n\nRearrange to form a quadratic equation:\n0 = $48 - 4S^2\n\nDivide through"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 78/100 done id=gsm8k_test_1022 prediction='12' gold='12' correct=True vote_counts={'12': 2, '30': 1, '60': 1, "Let's denote the number of small stuffed animals sold as S and the number of large stuffed animals sold as L. We know that Teresa sells the small stuffed animals at $4 each, so:\n\nTotal earnings from small stuffed animals = 4S\n\nTeresa sells 2L small stuffed animals (twice as many) compared to the number of large stuffed animals she sells. Therefore:\n\nNumber of small stuffed animals = Number of large stuffed animals × 2\nS = 2L\n\nWe also know that Teresa makes $120 in total from selling both types of stuffed animals:\n\nTotal earnings = Earnings from large stuffed animals + Earnings from small stuffed animals\n\nEarnings from large stuffed animals = $120 - Earnings from small stuffed animals\n\nSubstituting the known values:\n\n$120 = ($12/L) × L + (4S)\n\nSince we have two expressions for S and one expression for L, let's solve these equations together:\n\nFirst, let's express everything in terms of S:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - ($12/L) × L\n\nNow, let's simplify and substitute S with 2L:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $24/L\n\nWe know L = S / 2, so substitute L back into the equation:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $24/(S/2)\n\nSimplify further:\n(120 - 4S) = $120 - $48/S\n\nMultiply through by S to clear the fraction:\n120S - 4S^2 = $120S - $48\n\nRearrange to form a quadratic equation:\n0 = $48 - 4S^2\n\nDivide through": 1}
