[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 2/5 answer='First, we find how much land Abraham sold initially:\nHalf of the land was sold for $50, so each square meter cost $50 / 80 = $<<50/80=0.625>>0.625.\nHe then sold 1/4 of the land, which amounts to 80 / 4 = 20 square meters at $0.625 per square meter, totaling 20 * $0.625 = $<<20*0.625=12.5>>12.5.\n\nNext, we calculate the earnings from the last portion of his land, which is 1 - (0.5 + 0.25) = 0.25 or 20% of the total land area, priced at $3 per square meter, thus earning 20 * $3 = $<<20*3=60>>60.\n\nAdding up all these earnings gives us the total amount:\n$50 (first sale) + $12.5 (second sale) + $60 (third sale) = $<<50+12.5+60=122.5>>122.5\n\nAbraham was able to earn $122.5 after selling all his unused land.'
