[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 65/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many wheels Henry will have left, we first calculate the total number of wheels needed for the cars and motorcycles.\n\nFor the cars:\nEach car requires 4 wheels, so for 57 cars, the total number of wheels needed is 57 * 4 = 228 wheels.\n\nFor the motorcycles:\nEach motorcycle requires 2 wheels, so for 73 motorcycles, the total number of wheels needed is 73 * 2 = 146 wheels.\n\nNow, let's sum up the wheels needed for both cars and motorcycles:\n\nTotal wheels needed = Wheels for cars + Wheels for motorcycles\n                   = 228 + 146\n                   = 374 wheels\n\nHenry starts with a box containing 650 wheels. To find out how many wheels will be left after assembling all the toys, we subtract the total wheels needed from the initial amount:\n\nWheels left = Initial wheels + Wheels for cars + Wheels for motorcycles\n           = 650 + 374\n           = 1024 wheels\n\nTherefore, Henry will have 1024 wheels left after assembling all the toys."
