[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 1/3 answer='First, calculate the total area of the north wall:\n\\[ \\text{Area of North Wall} = 10 \\times 8 = 80 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nNext, calculate the total area of the south wall:\n\\[ \\text{Area of South Wall} = 10 \\times 8 = 80 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nNow, calculate the total area of the east wall:\n\\[ \\text{Area of East Wall} = 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nThen, calculate the total area of the west wall:\n\\[ \\text{Area of West Wall} = 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nAdd up all the areas to find the total area to be painted:\n\\[ \\text{Total Area} = 80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nSince one gallon covers 20 square feet, divide the total area by 20 to find out how many gallons are needed:\n\\[ \\text{Gallons Needed} = \\frac{240}{20} = 12 \\text{ gallons} \\]\n\nFinally, multiply the number of gallons by the price per gallon to find the total cost:\n\\[ \\text{Total Cost} = 12 \\times 12 = \\$\\boxed{144}\\]'
